  "prompt": "What is months at level in Accenture?",
  "response": "\"Months at Level\" in Accenture refers to the amount of time an employee has been at their current job level or grade. This metric is typically used in performance evaluations and career progression assessments. It helps managers track how long employees have been in their current role and can influence decisions about promotions, raises, and career development opportunities.\n\nThe specific details and implications of \"Months at Level\" can vary depending on the specific job level, department, and individual performance. Generally, spending a certain amount of time at a level before being considered for promotion is common in consulting and professional services firms like Accenture.",
